credit.credit-words: God in her palaces is known: His presence is her guard:

Confed’rate kings withdrew their siege, And of success despaired.
4.
They viewed her walls, admired and fled, With grief and terror struck;
Like women whom the sudden pangs Of travail had o’ertook.

No wretched crew of mariners Appear like them forlorn, When fleets from Tarshish’ wealthy coasts By eastern winds are torn.
6.
In Zion we have seen performed A work that was foretold, In pledge that God, for times to come, His city will uphold.

Let Zion’s mount with joy resound, Her daughters all be taught, In songs His judgments to extol, Who this deliv’rance wrought.
10.
This God is ours, and will be ours, Whilst we in Him confide; Who, as He has preserved us now, Till death will be our guide.
